.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-START 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-start \- start a hunk review session
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch start
[\fB\-U\fR \fIN\fR]
[\fB\-\-auto\-advance\fR|\fB\-\-no\-auto\-advance\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B start
finds the first unprocessed hunk, stores it as the selected change, and prints
it for review. If a session is already active, the command starts a fresh pass.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-U, \-\-unified=" N
Use
.I N
context lines in diff output. The default is 3.
.TP
.B \-\-auto\-advance
Set the session default so later action commands select the next hunk when
they finish.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-auto\-advance
Set the session default so later action commands leave no hunk selected when
they finish unless they opt back in.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-show (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-again (1)
